[8] Cholera, diarrhea - India (New Delhi)
Date: Sat 2 Jun 2007
Source: Sahara Samay News [edited]
<http://www.saharasamay.com/samayhtml/articles.aspx?newsid=76824>

With heat reaching its acme across northern India, waterborne epidemics
have begun spreading their tentacles in the [Indian] capital, Sahara Samay
sources said. According to the sources, cholera and diarrhea have gripped
many areas in Delhi. As many as 78 cases of waterborne diseases have been
reported in Central Zone.
Talking to the channel, a food inspector said that people should stay away
from sipping sugarcane juices and taking impure fruits, especially from
roadside vendors.
--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of India showing New Delhi, in the north, can be found at
<http://www.pnm.my/mtcp/images/maps/India-map.jpg>. - Mod.LL]
