[9] Cholera - India (Tamil Nadu)
Date: Sat 19 May 2007
Source: Chennai Online News [edited]
<http://www.chennaionline.com/colnews/newsitem.asp?NEWSID=%7B7F2D1F0D-AEEC-44E9-A495-B179869B05D7%7D&CATEGORYNAME=HEAL>

A 5 year old boy has died and more than 100 people are undergoing treatment
in various hospitals following an outbreak of cholera in the Chennai
district, official sources said. Around 70 people were rushed to hospitals
from Jalalpur village in the district. Many from Amrora, Mayagamo, and
Basayach villages were also admitted to hospitals following the outbreak of
the disease.
Chief medical officer, S C Maheshwari, said medical teams have been
dispatched to the affected villages.
--
communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Chennai (formerly Madras) is in north eastern state of Tamil Nadu, in
southern India. - Mod.LL]
